cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ST, cs.DS, cs.IT

This paper discusses the use of inductive conformal predictors, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistical inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses various modifications to achieve conditional validity, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses statistical inference, which falls under the category of Statistics (cs.ST) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses information theory, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
